                    <msContents>

                        <summary> M. Gullick suggests that the scribe was continental and that the
                            manuscript derives not from Christ Church, but from St Augustine’s,
                            Canterbury, the style of the initials on the opening leaves being
                            closest to those of Durham Cathedral Library MS B.II.16. At the end of
                            quire 12 is the contemporary note ‘medietas libri’. The manuscript has
                            the following additions (17th century): Ps.-Jerome, De nativitate Mariae
                            (1-3); letters of Pope Paschal II and Anselm of Canterbury (194v-196). </summary>

